#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:1
msgid "Image testing framework in `vtkTesting` has a new opt-in backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:3
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:5
msgid ""
"The VTK image testing framework has been enhanced to incorporate the "
"Structural Similarity Index (SSIM) metric on the Lab color space. This "
"contribution provides an opt-in feature to ensure that projects dependent on "
"VTK do not encounter broken tests when updating."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:7
msgid "SSIM Metric"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:9
msgid "Definition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:11
msgid ""
"The Structural Similarity Index (SSIM) is a metric introduced in the paper "
"titled \"Image Quality Assessment: From Error Visibility to Structural "
"Similarity\" by Wang et al. It measures the \"structural correlation\" "
"between two images, providing a comprehensive evaluation of their similarity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:13
msgid "Computation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:15
msgid ""
"In this implementation, SSIM is computed per pixel around a patch in the Lab "
"color space. The Lab color space is chosen for its perceptual uniformity, "
"ensuring that differences in color are consistent with human perception."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:17
msgid ""
"The SSIM metric produces a value between 0 and 1, where 1 indicates perfect "
"structural similarity between the images, and 0 indicates no similarity. "
"Domain of Output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:20
msgid ""
"The output of SSIM metric ranges from 0 to 1, where 1 indicates perfect "
"similarity, and 0 indicates no similarity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:22
msgid "Integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:24
msgid ""
"Users can enable this feature by defining the CMake variable "
"`DEFAULT_USE_SSIM_IMAGE_COMP` as true. When turned on, SSIM will be used by "
"default. Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:27
msgid "There are three ways to use the SSIM metric when setting a test:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:29
msgid "`TIGHT_VALID` (Default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:31
msgid ""
"Uses Euclidean metrics (L2 and 2-Wasserstein) on each channel. Computes the "
"maximum discrepancy (from 0 to 1). Recommended for images sensitive to "
"outliers. Default threshold is around 0.05."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:36
msgid "`LOOSE_VALID`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:38
msgid ""
"Uses both Manhattan distance and Earth-mover's distance on each channel. "
"Less sensitive to outliers. Suitable for images dependent on graphics "
"drivers or containing text. Default threshold is recommended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:44
msgid "`LEGACY_VALID`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:46
msgid ""
"Uses the old metric (not recommended). For compatibility with previous "
"testing methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:49
#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:66
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "範例："

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:51
msgid ""
"vtk_add_test_cxx(myModuleCxxTests tests\n"
"  Test1.cxx, LOOSE_VALID\n"
"  Test2.cxx # TIGHT_VALID by default\n"
"  Test3.cxx, LEGACY_VALID)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:58
msgid "Manual Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:60
msgid ""
"Tests added without using `vtk_add_test*` functions can still change the "
"metric using `set_tests_properties`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:62
msgid "Use `set_tests_properties` to set the environment variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:64
msgid ""
"Set `VTK_TESTING_IMAGE_COMPARE_METHOD` to one of the following values: "
"`TIGHT_VALID`, `LOOSE_VALID`, or `LEGACY_VALID`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:68
msgid ""
"set_tests_properties(Test1 PROPERTIES ENVIRONMENT \"VTK_TESTING=1;"
"VTK_TESTING_IMAGE_COMPARE_METHOD=LOOSE_VALID\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:72
msgid "Migration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/image-testing-framework.md:74
msgid ""
"It is advised to migrate to the new SSIM metric within a reasonable time "
"frame. The new metric is more selective and results in fewer false negatives "
"compared to the legacy method."
msgstr ""
